http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Police-nab-five-for-%E2%80%98organising-cockfight%E2%80%99/article14000729.ece

The Aswaraopet police raided a farm at Vutlapalli and arrested five persons for organising the banned sport of cockfighting in connection with Sankranti festivities in the village on Thursday.Acting on a tip-off, a police team rushed to Vutlapalli and seized roosters engaged in cockfighting by five persons on the outskirts of the village in the afternoon.The police detained the accused, and seized their mobile phones and motorbikes, besides some cash from their possession.Meanwhile, the Sattupalli sub-division police have stepped up vigil in the areas bordering Andhra Pradesh to keep the banned sport in check.